{"id":7878,"date":"2012-10-10T10:46:36","date_gmt":"2012-10-10T14:46:36","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=7878"},"modified":"2025-03-03T11:40:49","modified_gmt":"2025-03-03T07:40:49","slug":"musa-moses-patience-harm","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/10\/musa-moses-patience-harm\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Musa: Moses hurt by people, but was patient"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, was distributing charity when a man from the Ansar said, \u201cBy Allah, Muhammad did not intend to please Allah with this!\u201d I came to the Prophet and told him about it, then anger could be seen on his face. Then, the Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Who would be just if Allah and His Messenger are not just?<\/strong>&#8221; Then, the Prophet said, &#8220;<strong>May Allah have mercy on<\/strong> <strong>Moses! He was hurt by more than this, yet he was patient<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 3405, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1062<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em><strong>Muttafaqun Alayhi<\/strong><\/em> (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0633\u0652\u0639\u064f\u0648\u062f\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0642\u0650\u0633\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0629\u064b \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064c \u0645\u0650\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0635\u064e\u0627\u0631\u0650 \u0648\u064